erfowl.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_253\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"620\" caption=\"Oh to be in the Floating Allotment in the Summer Time\"]<a href=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Screen-shot-2011-06-16-at-16.27.54.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-253\" title=\"Pop Up Cafe Back in Kingsland Basin\" src=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Screen-shot-2011-06-16-at-16.27.54-620x347.png\" alt=\"The floating allotment\" width=\"620\" height=\"347\" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe Cafe will be open from 12 Noon to 5 Pm\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>The dates are as Follows:</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>15 June</strong>: Cafe\r\nWorkshop: How to save a baby\'s life\r\n\r\nlifesaving and CPR.\r\n\r\n<strong>20 July</strong> - Cafe\r\nWorkshop to be announced\r\n\r\n<strong>17 August</strong> -Cafe\r\nConstructing growing screens\r\n\r\nfloating planters how to make and construction day.\r\n\r\n<strong>21 and 22 September</strong> - Cafe\r\nOpen House London - open boats\r\n\r\n<strong>19 October</strong> - Cafe\r\nHow to make your own soap and why it\'s better than the soap from shops\r\n\r\nSo if it\'s just to come and have a cup of tea and read the newspapers or look at the floating allotment or our bees. We welcome you throughout the summer.\r\n\r\nLook forward to seeing you here!','CHUG Pop Up Cafe','','publish','open','open','','chug-pop-up-cafe','','','2013-06-05 20:21:32','2013-06-05 19:21:32','',0,'http://chug.org.uk/?p=217',0,'post','',0),(301,1,'2013-07-15 13:53:34','2013-07-15 12:53:34','Chug had a great day at the Shoreditch festival on Hoxton Market.\r\n\r\nChildren and adults alike joined in with traditional canal painting of roses and castles on plates.\r\n\r\nHomemade cakes looked delicious and were sold, and all donations collected were towards laburnum boat club\'s fund towards a new fleet of boats. Plates made great decoration, enjoyed by the chug community at our annual party.\r\n