gates (sometimes backwards) in a particular sequence</span><em><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">Â  </span><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">- </span></em>in the shortest time possible.\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">The course is being built primarily for the use of the many local children and young people who attend the <strong>Laburnum Boat Club</strong> just along the canal. The Laburnum Boat Club (a small charity) is a community-based watersports centre set up by local parents thirty years ago. The Club has an active <em>Canoe Slalom Team</em> that has been competing in events around the South East all year. They are led by one of the Club\'s senior members - 18 year old Vanessa Humphries. They are all very keen and work hard but at the moment they<em> have nowhere to practice.</em></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">This is why CHUG are coming to the rescue. CHUG are committed to protecting the waterways in the borough and enabling local people to get access to them and enjoy them. Using their own efforts and fund-raised resources they have designed, and are in process of building, a terrific new slalom course for the kids to train on. The course should be completed in the coming months, and will be a valuable asset for local children - encouraging them to take exercise, enjoy a constructive leisure time, and appreciate the canal and its environs.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"text-align: center;\">Canoe Slalom is a worldwide sport and Great Britain won two medals (one gold and one silver) at the Olympics twelve months ago (watched by the Boat Club\'s slalom team!).</span></p>\nLaburnum Boat Club are one of the best clubs for local kids, and are proud to be one of their partners. Visit their websiteÂ <a href=\"http://www.laburnumboatclub.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.laburnumboatclub.com</a>Â andÂ find out about more activities. On the news page Â you can also see how you can donate through shopping online: \"Give as you live\". Help Laburnum buy their badly needed next fleet of kayaks, by just shopping online!\n\n<a href=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/slalom3.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-338 alignleft\" title=\"slalom3\" src=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/slalom3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"324\" height=\"576\" /></a><a href=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/slalom-5.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-337 alignleft\" title=\"slalom 5\" src=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/slalom-5.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"324\" height=\"576\" /></a><a href=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/slalom-4.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-336 alignleft\" title=\"slalom 4\" src=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/slalom-4.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"324\" height=\"576\" /></a><a href=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/slalom-2.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-335 alignleft\" title=\"slalom 2\" src=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/slalom-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"324\" height=\"576\" /></a><a href=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/slalom-1.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-334 alignleft\" title=\"slalom 1\" src=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/slalom-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"324\" height=\"576\" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;','Slalom Course at Kingsland Basin','','inherit','open','open','','320-autosave','','','2015-03-26 15:08:43','2015-03-26 15:08:43','',320,'http://chug.org.uk/2013/08/320-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(339,1,'2013-08-09 10:28:56','2013-08-09 09:28:56','&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe at chug are so proud of Hannah (chug resident) who\'s current adventure is walking around the entire recently opened Welsh Coastal Path with a donkey!\r\n\r\nHere\'s a clip from the North Wales daily post....\r\n\r\nYou can also follow her highly amusing journey on www.seasidedonkey.co.uk\r\n<a href=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Hannah-donkey-p