ing in the basin last year, so the Wildlife and Gardening group is working to reestablish wildflowers for the benefit of our bees, and bring back other flora and fauna on the island.\r\n\r\nCheck out the Wildlife and Gardening group hard at work:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/islandlookingout.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-329\" title=\"View from Andy Bees Island\" src=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/islandlookingout-620x465.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"620\" height=\"465\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/islandcleanup.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-330\" title=\"Wildlife and gardening group members hard at work on the island!\" src=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/islandcleanup-620x465.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"620\" height=\"465\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThey even fished an old bike from the canal!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/trashcanal.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-331\" title=\"Pulling rubbish from the canal \" src=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/trashcanal-620x465.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"620\" height=\"465\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Wildlife and Gardening Group Workday','','publish','open','open','','wildlife-and-gardening-group-workday','','','2013-07-19 14:01:56','2013-07-19 13:01:56','',0,'http://chug.org.uk/?p=327',0,'post','',0),(317,1,'2013-07-15 13:51:38','2013-07-15 12:51:38','','photo-10','','inherit','open','open','','photo-10','','','2013-07-15 13:51:38','2013-07-15 12:51:38','',301,'http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/photo-10.jpg',3,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(312,1,'2013-07-15 13:46:21','2013-07-15 12:46:21','','photo-6','','inherit','open','open','','photo-6','','','2013-07-15 13:46:21','2013-07-15 12:46:21','',301,'http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/photo-6.jpg',8,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(313,1,'2013-07-15 13:47:03','2013-07-15 12:47:03','','photo-7','','inherit','open','open','','photo-7','','','2013-07-15 13:47:03','2013-07-15 12:47:03','',301,'http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/photo-7.jpg',7,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(315,1,'2013-07-15 13:48:19','2013-07-15 12:48:19','','photo-9','','inherit','open','open','','photo-9','','','2013-07-15 13:48:19','2013-07-15 12:48:19','',301,'http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/photo-9.jpg',5,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(316,1,'2013-07-15 13:48:53','2013-07-15 12:48:53','','chug','','inherit','open','open','','chug-2','','','2013-07-15 13:48:53','2013-07-15 12:48:53','',301,'http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/chug.jpg',4,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(318,1,'2013-07-15 13:52:15','2013-07-15 12:52:15','','photo-11','','inherit','open','open','','photo-11','','','2013-07-15 13:52:15','2013-07-15 12:52:15','',301,'http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/photo-11.jpg',2,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(320,1,'2013-08-07 10:11:25','2013-08-07 09:11:25','<strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.0pt;\">Canoe Slalom Course at Kingsland Basin</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"></strong><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">This year</span> CHUG<span style=\"text-align: justify;\">Â are building a Canoe Slalom Course in Kingsland Basin.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-align: justify;\">The slalom course is a series of pairs of light poles suspended from overhead wires forming \"gates\" that the canoes have to negotiate.</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">Â  </span><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">The paddler and the canoe (or kayak) have to travel through each of the gates (sometimes backwards) in a particular sequence</span><em><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">Â  </span><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">- </span></em>in the shortest time possible.\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">The course is being built primarily for the use of the many local children and young people who attend the <strong>Laburnum Boat Club</strong> just along the canal. The Laburnum Boat Club (a small charity) is a community-based watersports centre set up by local parents thirty years ago. The Club has an active <em>Canoe Slalom Team</em> that has been competing in events around the South East all year. They are led by one of the Club\'s senior members - 18 year old Vanessa Humphries. They are all very keen and work hard but at the moment they<em> have nowhere to practice.</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">This is why CHUG are coming to the rescue. CHUG are committed to protecting the waterways in the borough and enabling local people to get access to them and enjoy them. Using their own efforts and fund-raised resources they have designed, and are in process of building, a terrific new slalom course for the kids to train on. The course should be completed in the coming months, and will be a valuable asset for local children - encouraging them to take exercise, enjoy a constructive leisure time, and appreciate the canal and its environs.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"text-align: center;\">Canoe Slalom is a worldwide sport and Great Britain won two medals (one gold and one silver) at the Olympics twelve months ago (watched by the Boat Club\'s slalom team!).</span></p>\r\nLaburnum Boat Club are one of the best clubs for local kids, and are proud to be one of their partners. Visit their websiteÂ <a href=\"http://www.laburnumboatclub.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.laburnumboatclub.com</a>Â andÂ find out about more activities. On the news page Â you can also see how you can donate through shopping online: \"Give as you live\". Help Laburnum buy their badly needed next fleet of kayaks, by just shopping online!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/slalom3.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-338 alignleft\" title=\"slalom3\" src=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/slalom3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"324\" height=\"576\" /></a><a href=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/slalom-5.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-337 alignleft\" title=\"slalom 5\" src=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/slalom-5.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"324\" height=\"576\" /></a><a href=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/slalom-4.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-336 alignleft\" title=\"slalom 4\" src=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/slalom-4.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"324\" height=\"576\" /></a><a href=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/slalom-2.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-335 alignleft\" title=\"slalom 2\" src=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/slalom-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"324\" height=\"576\" /></a><a href=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/slalom-1.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-334 alignleft\" title=\"slalom 1\" src=\"http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/slalom-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"324\" height=\"576\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Slalom Course at Kingsland Basin','','publish','open','open','','slalom-course-at-kingsland-basin','','','2015-03-26 15:31:09','2015-03-26 15:31:09','',0,'http://chug.org.uk/?p=320',0,'post','',0),(427,1,'2014-07-12 16:04:48','2014-07-12 15:04:48','','Screen Shot 2014-07-12 at 16.03.36','','inherit','open','open','','screen-shot-2014-07-12-at-16-03-36','','','2014-07-12 16:04:48','2014-07-12 15:04:48','',320,'http://chug.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Screen-Shot-2014-07-12-at-16.03.36.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(321,1,'2015-04-20 10:28:48','2015-04-20 09:28:48','Chug had a great day at the Shoreditch festival on Hoxton Market.\r\n\r\nChildren and adults alike joined in with traditional canal painting of roses and castles on plates.\r\n\r\nHomemade cakes looked delicious and were sold, and all donations collected were towards laburnum boat c