s will be set on a case-by-case basis according to the nature and requirements of the project, with a percentage of the grant to be given at the outset, a percentage on completion and agreed regular amounts to be paid through the project</li>\r\n	<li>â€¢ progress will be reviewed at regular intervals throughout the project by two or more members of CHUG</li>\r\n	<li>â€¢ written proof of the use of funds will be required, in the form of receipts, reports from the organiser/s or other as requested by CHUG</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">How to apply for a grant.</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThere is no deadline for applications, which will be assessed in the order in which they are received.\r\n\r\nThere is no set format for applications, though each must present the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>â€¢ name of project</li>\r\n	<li>â€¢ brief description: What is it and how would it work?</li>\r\n	<li>â€¢ what is it about the project that excites you?</li>\r\n	<li>â€¢ how would it impact on the canal and who would benefit most from the project?</li>\r\n	<li>â€¢ what is the life of the project? How long would the results last?</li>\r\n	<li>â€¢ any imagery that would help illustrate the project and bring it to life for CHUG?</li>\r\n	<li>â€¢ outline budget</li>\r\n	<li>â€¢ why should CHUG fund the project?</li>\r\n	<li>â€¢ would CHUG be the only funder; if not, who else would support the project? (CHUG would not want to be associated with co-funders that clashed with its objectives and ethos.)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAll CHUG-funded projects would be used by CHUG to promote its own work on Hackneyâ€™s canals.\r\n\r\nFor further information about the grants programme, or for guidance in making an application, please email info@chug.org.uk.\r\n\r\nWe look forward to hearing from you!\r\n\r\n*','CHUG Grants','','publish','open','open','','chug-grants','','','2016-03-18 21:52:47','2016-03-18 21:52:47','',0,'http://chug.org.uk/?p=525',0,'post',